						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">13th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record registers a grant of one out of two oil-mills for a perpetual lamp to be burnt before the god. The beginning portion of the record probably engraved on the top of the pillar is broken and missing.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 13th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
